To clone the repository in Remote :- 
     Go to the repository from where we need to clone -> Click Fork -> Create Fork
     (Git_GitHub repository is cloned in remote repository)


To Clone the repository Locally :-
     Go to terminal or Git bash -> configure the git details
     To Configure git user details :
        git config --global user.name "Your Name"
        git config --global user.email "your-email@example.com"
     Initialize git :- git init
     Copy the Git_GitHub repository URL from the remote cloned repository
     Clone the repository:- git clone <repository_URL>


Change directory to Repository name :- cd Git_GitHub

Move file to stagging area :- git add .

Move file to commit :- git commit -m "Clone repository file created"

git status

git push
